HEADWORD: Epacris
<hw>Ep"a*cris</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧p"⟦adot⟧*kr⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from Gr. <grk>'e`pakros</grk> pointed at the end. So called
in allusion to the sharply pointed leaves.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus of shrubs, natives of Australia, New Zealand, etc., having
pretty white, red, or purple blossoms, and much resembling
heaths.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

